content:
When setting up your Channel Menu, keep these restrictions and considerations in mind.

The Channel Menu is available in Lightning Experience and requires the Performance, Professional, Unlimited, or Essentials edition.

Usage limitations and restrictions for the Channel Menu:

* Only one Messaging for Web channel per Channel Menu is supported.
* User Verification won't work within the channel menu when a Messaging for Web deployment is added.
* Only one Embedded Service chat type can be selected in the same Channel Menu.
* Phone numbers must include a + sign with the country code for international customers.
* WhatsApp requires customers to install the native client version from whatsapp.com.
* The latest static files can be used by hard reloading or clearing cache and refreshing the web page.
* Web Chat only setups require an additional step to bring agents online before validating.
* Experiences require the CSP Trusted Site in Service Setup and the Trusted Site for Scripts in Experience Builder to be configured separately.
* Static Resources must be tested in the builder to discover any CSP errors.
* Changes to the Channel Menu setup may take up to 10 minutes to appear on your website due to caching.
title: Channel Menu Limitations and Setup Considerations in Service Cloud
